This was an amazing Mom and Pop brink and mortor restaurant back in the day, but since it has been upgraded and remodeled the menu has been downgraded and the food isn't as good as back in the day. My friend and I recently visited El Tamarindo because of their Meatless Monday menu. I really wanted to love this place because I think it's great they offer a big selection of vegan options on Mondays. The food tasted okay, but unfortunately I had a bad food reaction that day. I am very sensitive to bell peppers and told my server that I couldn't eat them and asked to confirm that there were no bell peppers in the food I ordered. He assured me that there weren't, but there definitely was a bell peppers that made its way somewhere, or there was a contamination. Anyways, I ended up very ill that night and into the morning. If you're not sensitive to any food ingredients and are looking for a reasonably priced, decent food, then this could be a good spot for you. But if you have any extra dietary restrictions then I would be hesitant to trust the kitchen, at least based on the one experience I had. Also, this isn't a great place for good cocktails if that's your thing. I love margaritas, but they use margaritasix for many of their drinks, and it's gross.

Long-time favorite with great El Salvidorian food. The papusas are so delicious...everyone of them is a hit and the price is right (under $3 each). The papusas are served with a nice vinegar slaw and red sauce (akin to tomato sauce with a mildly sweet favor). Great combination with the saltiness of the papusas.  Lots of vegetarian options on the menu and dishes that can be converted to vegetarian with slight adjustments.  The red sangria is a must. Get a pitcher, you'll be glad you did. They have a nice specialty cocktail menu too. - great for groups - friendly staff - great food

Literally the worst experience I have ever had at a restaurant.  I have Celiac, and asked for my trios enchilada meal to be gluten free. They brought out the dish vegetarian, which I did not ask for. I only mentioned gluten. They went back, and brought it out again. This time, the order had beans mixed in, which I specifically asked to be not on the plate. They went back again, and brought out all 3 enchiladas with chicken. At that point, I just told them to not even bother bringing my food again. The manager brought out my food the second and third times, and continuously blamed the waiter. It was extremely unprofessional and off-putting, especially considering the manager himself messed up multiple times. He just continued to make excuses instead of taking any responsibility.  My friend then found a piece of metal in her pupusa. It turned out to be part of a sponge.  Finally, we went to split the bill with separate credit cards. They, somehow, decided to charge everything on one person's card. It is unclear if it was an accident. We kept asking what happened, and they were being extremely evasive. We finally received an answer as to what happened. When we did, we had to ask multiple times for a void receipt. We finally received it. It took the restaurant a week to confirm with the credit card company that the purchase was void. Additionally, the first charge somehow had a $30 tip for a $70 something meal. It was really strange.
